[0.000, "o", ">>> Command: ./piharness.sh skill show deploy\r\n    Shows the deploy skill's full instructions.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.011, "o", "── Skill: deploy ──\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "---\r\nname: deploy\r\nversion: 1\r\ncreated: 2026-07-08\r\nusage_count: 0\r\ntrigger_patterns: [deploy, deployment, publish, go live, ship]\r\ndescription: \"Deploy a developed application to production. Captures build, test, deploy, and rollback patterns.\"\r\n---\r\n# Skill: deploy\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nAn application is developed but not yet deployed, or needs a repeatable deployment\r\npipeline. Manual deployment is error-prone, not reproducible, and blocks overnight\r\nself-evolution.\r\n\r\n## Pattern\r\nUse the PIHARNESS pipeline to deploy:\r\n\r\n1. **Build** — Compile/package the app using its native build tool.\r\n2. **Test** — Run the test suite via a tester worker.\r\n3. **Deploy** — Push the artifact to the target environment.\r\n4. **Verify** — Smoke-test the deployment.\r\n5. **Rollback** — If verification fails, revert to the previous version.\r\n\r\nRun it:\r\n```bash\r\npiharness deploy <app-name> [--env production|staging]\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr use the pipeline for review-gated deployment:\r\n```bash\r\npiharness pipeline \"Deploy <app> to <env>\" --"]
[0.000, "o", "rounds 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Prevention\r\n- Always test before deploying — never skip verification.\r\n- Keep deployment configuration (env vars, secrets) in a `.deploy/` directory.\r\n- Use the `self-evolve` system to capture repeated deployment patterns as new skills.\r\n- Run `piharness nightly` after deployment to log the task and trigger pattern extraction.\r\n- Prefer `piharness auto` or `piharness supervise` for unattended deployments so\r\n  the runtime chain handles failures gracefully.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.098, "o", "\r\n>>> Command: ./piharness.sh learn suggest\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    Suggests new skills based on task pattern clusters.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.111, "o", "No patterns detected yet — keep working!\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n>>> Skills are the heart of PIHARNESS self-evolution:\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    - Repeated tasks auto-extract into reusable skills\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    - Skills include trigger patterns, description, and usage count\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    - The orchestrator checks skills before spawning workers\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    - Overnight 'nightly' maintenance evolves the skill library\r\n\r\n==============================================\r\n  Demo 7 Complete\r\n==============================================\r\n"]
